@startuml
' Deployment diagram for Project-AI

node "User Machine" as UserMachine {
  component "Desktop App\n(PyQt6)" as Desktop
  database "Local Data\n(data/)" as LocalData
}

node "Cloud / Server" as Cloud {
  component "Web Backend\n(Flask)" as Backend
  database "Cloud Sync DB\n(Postgres/Redis)" as CloudDB
  node "Storage" as BlobStorage
}

node "External APIs" as External {
  component "OpenAI API" as OpenAI
  component "SMTP" as SMTP
}

Desktop --> LocalData : stores user data, memories, models
Desktop --> Backend : HTTPS API (sync, auth, predictions)
Backend --> CloudDB : persist user data, devices, sync state
Backend --> BlobStorage : store uploaded assets (images)
Backend --> OpenAI : generative requests (optional)
Backend --> SMTP : send emergency alerts

' Deployment notes
note over UserMachine
 - Desktop app optional offline
 - Cloud sync via secure TLS and JWT
end note

@enduml
